<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-137-191 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 975 160</DOCID><JOURNAL>CAD-CAM International  June 1991 v10 n6 p31(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Dated performer. (Software Review) (Micro Cadam) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Grant, Nick.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>CADAM Inc's Micro Cadam is a microcomputer-based 2D and 3Dcomputer-aided drafting and design package aimed at electrical andmechanical engineers.andP;  It requires an 80386-based microcomputerwith 4Mbytes of extended memory and a 20Mbyte hard disk.andO;Installation is easy, although memory may be a problem in somemachines because Micro Cadam requires that RAM be in extendedrather than expanded mode.andP;  The 2D module, Micro Cadam Plus,suffers from a crude and dated interface but offers accurategeometric positioning, dimensioning and overlaying.andP;  Micro Cadam3D, the 3D module, is a separate package and has essentially thesame interface with somewhat similar menus.andP;  Features includeextruding and revolving profiles, powerful surface creation toolsand the ability to create primitives.andP;  Micro Cadam providesexcellent functionality but is awkward to use.andP;  Prices are 2,995pounds sterling for Micro Cadam Plus and 3,495 pounds sterling forMicro Cadam 3D.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   CADAM Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   Micro Cadam (CAD software).andO;Topic:     Computer-Aided DesignGraphics SoftwareDownloadingMicro-Mainframe Communication.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Quick view. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>